<subSubSection pageId="13" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[173,660,353,1172]" pageId="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,311,1097,1118]" pageId="13">Etymology.</emphasis>
The trivial name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2014" box="[512,571,1097,1118]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gilvus">
<emphasis box="[512,571,1097,1118]" italics="true" pageId="13">gilvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= pale yellow) is a Latin adjective that refers to the apex of the last antennomere.
</paragraph>
